 journalists have influenced and been denied influence to the content, presentation, and very nature of news. Through anecdotes culled from interviews with over 100 broadcast and print journalists, Newkirk exposes the trials and triumphs of African American journalists as they struggle in pursuit of more equitable coverage of racial minorities. She illuminates the agonizing dilemmas they face when writing stories critical of blacks, stories which force them to choose between journalistic integrity, their own advancement, and the almost certain enmity of the black community. Within the Veil is a gripping front-line report on the continuing battle to integrate America's newsrooms and news coverage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican American journalistsvBiography. 0aAfrican Americans in the newspaper industry. 0aAfrican AmericansxPress coverage. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh  aAfrican.  aAmerican.  aacross.  acoverage.  aequitable.  ajournalists.  aminorities.  amore.  anewsrooms.  apursuit.  aracial.  astruggle.  athey.  atrials.  atriumps.1 aBell, Derrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475799440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814759134.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814759134423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814759134/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LB  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK